edu.umn.cs.spatialHadoop.mapred

Class SpatialRecordReader<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umn.cs.spatialHadoop.mapred.SpatialRecordReader<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.hadoop.mapred.RecordReader<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RTreeRecordReader, ShapeArrayRecordReader, ShapeIterRecordReader, ShapeLineRecordReader, ShapeRecordReader

    public abstract class SpatialRecordReader<K,V>
extends Object
implements org.apache.hadoop.mapred.RecordReader<K,V>
    A base class to read shapes from files. It reads either single shapes, list of shapes, or R-trees. It automatically detects the format of the underlying block and parses it accordingly. The class implement the RecordReader interface allowing it to be used in MapReduce programs with an appropriate InputFormat. The key is always a Rectangle that indicates the MBR of the corresponding partition. In case of a non-indexed file, the key is an invalid rectangle. See Rectangle.isValid().
    Author:
    Ahmed Eldawy
    See Also:
    ShapeLineRecordReader, ShapeRecordReader, ShapeArrayRecordReader, RTreeRecordReader

        protected boolean initializeReader()
                            throws IOException
        Initializes the reader to read from the input stream or file. First, it initializes the MBR of the partition being read if the file is globally indexed. It also detects whether the file is R-tree indexed or not which allows it to skip the R-tree if not needed to be read.

      • nextShape

        protected boolean nextShape(Shape s)
                     throws IOException
        Reads next shape from input and returns true. If no more shapes are left in the split, a false is returned. This function first reads a line by calling the method nextLine(Text) then parses the returned line by calling TextSerializable.fromText(Text) on that line. If no stock shape is set, a NullPointerException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        s -
        Returns:
        Throws:

      • nextShapes

        protected boolean nextShapes(org.apache.hadoop.io.ArrayWritable shapes)
                      throws IOException
        Reads all shapes left in the current block in one shot. This function runs a loop where it keeps reading shapes by calling the method nextShape(Shape) until one of the following conditions happen. 1. The whole file is read. No more records to read. 2. Number of parsed records reaches the threshold defined by the configuration parameter spatialHadoop.mapred.MaxShapesPerRead. To disable this check, set the configuration parameter to -1 3. Total size of parsed data from file reaches the threshold defined by the configuration parameter spatialHadoop.mapred.MaxBytesPerRead. To disable this check, set the configuration parameter to -1.
        Parameters:
        shapes -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        IOException

      • nextRTree

        protected boolean nextRTree(RTree<? extends Shape> rtree)
                     throws IOException
        Reads the next RTree from file. The file must be part of an R-tree index. If the file is not locally indexed using an R-tree, a runtime exception is thrown. If the file is locally indexed using an R-tree, the R-tree is consumed from the file and parsed by calling RTree.readFields(DataInput) on the input stream.
